What have we all learned about this writing prompt that we all expeirced? Well, I can assure you that I never thought i could type as fast as i did in this survey. I will be talking about this writing prompt and what i learned about myself. 

Remember when we had our old computer classes to teach us how to use the keyboard, and if we achieved a certain goal you would be rewarded a certificate. I was horrible at typing when i was kid, but taking this survey, i learned that over the years i was able to remember the placements of different keys.  I think this survey really opened my eyes to know that i can type fast. This survey has brought memories that i haven't thought about in that specific class years ago.  I am super surprised that i have this ability to type fast, and it opened my eyes that there are so many opportunities out there for people who type fast, "as in jobs i mean of course''. 

I  don't realy have agruments about this prompt writing survey to be honest.  I really enjoyed doing this survey, and being able to remember old memories about school. I hope you other people have enjoyed this survey just much as i did. This really opened my eyes, and I hope it opened yours too.

Today's society is very scary, well why do I say that about today's reality.  Well one example is when we have social media telling our kids of (today's society) to be this or to be that, and if you do not meet those standards like every other kid, they will be considred not cool.  Kids these days have cell phones at a early age, and they get into social media platforms like tik-tok or facebook, and even instagram.
